<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED38A08FC96F89B" blockId="15.[216,1203,1569,2346]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
Type locality. 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30861D6B3BFDD08A08FDC1F93F" box="[520,603,1660,1700]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" unit="km" value="4.0">4 km</quantity>
south-east of 'Rangari' homestead, on the Gunnedah-Barraba roadside, 
<quantity id="4CBA9B30861D6B3BFC8E8ADFFC5EF949" box="[854,964,1707,1746]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" unit="km" value="34.0">34 km</quantity>
north-east of Gunnedah, NSW (Locality 18).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED28B73FBE8F8C7" blockId="15.[216,1203,1569,2346]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Stratigraphic position. In bioclastic limestone, the middle limestone lens in the Tulcumba Sandstone.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED18B17FCB7F87C" blockId="15.[216,1203,1569,2346]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
Additional material. 
<specimenCount id="9D44FD5C861D6B3BFD4A8B17FCC8F810" box="[658,850,1891,1931]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" type="generic">1 specimen</specimenCount>
each from north of 'Rangari' (Locality 14), north-east of 'Rangari' (Locality 15) and Glenbawn (Locality 29).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED18B9AFB13F78E" blockId="15.[216,1203,1569,2346]" box="[265,1161,2030,2069]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Geographic distribution. 'Rangari' to Glenbawn.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED18468FBB2F7DF" blockId="15.[216,1203,1569,2346]" box="[265,1064,2076,2116]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Geological age. Middle to late Tournaisian.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED0843FFC60F73B" blockId="15.[216,1203,1569,2346]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
Etymology. Derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BFCAA843FFB89F7E9" box="[882,1043,2123,2162]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">elongatus</emphasis>
meaning elongate, referring to the tall spire of shell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFED184D3FB9BF6B1" blockId="15.[216,1203,1569,2346]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
Remarks. This species is characterised by a tall-spired shell with a rather flat whorl profile, which is very different from any other 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BFD7D8577FCF3F6B1" box="[677,873,2307,2346]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Hesperieua" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BFD7D8577FCF3F6B1" box="[677,873,2307,2346]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">HesperieUa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
